        "answer": "$2x \\cos(x^2)$",
        "explanation": [
            "1. Identify the outer function $u = \\sin(v)$ and inner function $v = x^2$.",
            "2. Apply the chain rule: $f'(x) = u'(v) \\cdot v'(x)$.",
            "3. $u'(v) = \\cos(v)$ and $v'(x) = 2x$.",
            "4. Substitute back: $f'(x) = \\cos(x^2) \\cdot 2x = 2x \\cos(x^2)$."
